-- T-Mobile’s Czech Unit First-Half Revenue Declines 3.5 Percent
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2012-08-09T08:51:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-09/t-mobile-s-czech-unit-first-half-revenue-declines-3-5-percent.html
T-Mobile International AG’s Czech
unit said first-half revenue fell 3.5 percent to 12.9 billion
koruna ($634 million) as prices of telecommunication services
and average revenue per user declined.  Adjusted Ebitda, or earnings before interest, taxes,
depreciation and amortization, fell 10 percent to 6.03 billion
koruna in the six months ended June 30, the Prague-based company
said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague at 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
